    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="621"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.61231/2–2850</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador of the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Panyushkin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the Ambassador
                    of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics and has the honor to refer to the
                    Embassy’s <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of February 28, 1950 <pb
                        facs="1140" n="1124" xml:id="pg_1124"/> concerning the inspection of
                    personal baggage of diplomatic couriers arriving at New York.</p>
                <p>A communication has been addressed to the Treasury Department<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d621fn1">A letter dated March 16 was sent to the Secretary of the
                        Treasury John W. Snyder; not printed.</note> requesting that consideration
                    be given to the granting of blanket authorization to the Collector of Customs at
                    New York for the clearance, on a basis of reciprocity, of the personal baggage
                    of Soviet diplomatic couriers. As soon as a reply is received the Ambassador
                    will be informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-16">March 16,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
